translated:
Östling, Gustav Adolf (Gösta), central librarian, Borås, b. May 13, 1902 in Stockholm to Gustaf Ö. and Edla Larsson. Married on May 30, m. Sigrid Ramström. Children: Sven b. 1931, Kerstin b. 1934, Erik b. 1938, Eva b. 1944. — Bachelor of Arts from Uppsala University, 1925. Traveled to Denmark in 1930. City librarian in Uppsala from 1927 to 1930, central librarian in Borås from 1930. Secretary of the Nordic Association's Borås branch from 1938-1943, vice chairman of the West Gothia sports association from 1943-1946, secretary of the Borås Rotary Club from 1943-1947, chairman of the Literary Society in Borås from 1946, member of the board for technical gymnastics from 1946, secretary of the Swedish General Library Association from 1947. Editor for the Library Magazine from 1948. Writings: articles in the Library Magazine. Member of the Swedish National Biography Society. 

Östlund, Crispin Gustaf, dentist, Limmared, b. October 25, 1898 in Trollhättan to book printer Lars Johan Ö. and Maria Eleonora Wennergren. Married on May 30, m. Petra Ingvarda Sörensen.— Graduated from Vänersborgs High School in 1918, studied medicine from 1918-1922, dental candidate in 1930, dentist in 1933. Practice in Limmared and Länghem. Vice chairman of the Odontological Society from 1930-1931, chairman and curator from 1931-1932.
